NORMALISED EXTRACT

Key technical points (implementation-ready):
- Export forms (ECMAScript modules): named exports, default export, aggregated/re-exporting, export list, export declarations for variables, functions, classes, and destructured bindings.
- Syntax variants (exact):
  - Export declarations: export let name1, name2; export const name = 1; export function f() {} export class C {}.
  - Export list: export { name1, name2 as alias }.
  - Default export: export default expression; export default function f() {}; export { existing as default }.
  - Aggregating/re-exporting: export * from "module"; export { name } from "module"; export { default as name } from "module"; export * as ns from "module".
- Semantics: exports are declarations producing live bindings; export statements are static and hoisted as declarations (value not required at declaration time).
- Errors: duplicate exported names or more than one default export cause SyntaxError at parse/evaluation time.

